title: Seeds announced for Euro 2016 playoffs
text:
Seeds announced for Euro 2016 playoffs Source: Shanghai Daily | October 15, 2015, Thursday | Print Edition 
Bosnia, Ukraine, Sweden and Hungary will be the four seeded teams for the Euro 2016 playoffs when the draw is made on Sunday, UEFA announced yesterday. 
They will be paired with the four other third-placed teams from the just-concluded group stages â€” Denmark, Ireland, Norway and Slovenia. In all 24 teams will contest the Euro finals in France next summer. The top two teams from the nine qualifying groups made it through as well as Turkey, as the best third-placed team. That left four places to be decided in two leg playoffs, contested by the rest of the teams placing third. The first legs will be held from November 12-14 with the return on November 15-17.
